) differs clearly from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[734,835,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[734,835,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[849,929,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[171,1411,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[159,1428,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Polymixis spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 21 in BBT; 22 in ZFMK (photo by D. Stüning); 23 in HNHM (photo by Zs. Balint &amp; G. Katona)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089293/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) in its subapically dilated valva with the more prominent dorsal costal protrusion and the somewhat less elongate cucullus with a more rounded apex, whereas the distal section of the valva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[474,576,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[474,576,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is narrowed, the dorsal costal protrusion is less prominent and narrower, and the tip of the cucullus is somewhat more elongate. The left digitus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[932,1091,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[932,1091,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is wide and more or less lobelike, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[332,434,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[332,434,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is narrower and consisting of two separated narrow lobes directed distally and ventrally. The right digitus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[377,537,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[377,537,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clavate, directed distally and having a short and thin dorsal lobe, whereas the largest lobe of that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[396,498,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[396,498,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is curved ventrally and the smallest one is directed dorsally. The clavi of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are asymmetrical and thick, whereas those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[729,832,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[729,832,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are narrow and symmetrical. Additionally, the dorsal margin of the sacculus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[438,597,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[438,597,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less concave and the clasper is markedly narrower than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[1278,1380,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[1278,1380,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[289,447,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[289,447,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[668,770,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[668,770,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dentate tip of the carina which is smooth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[1328,1430,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[1328,1430,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The vesicae of the two species display no remarkable differences. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1169,1330,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[1169,1330,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,185,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[205,1382,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Polymixis spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 30, 33–35 in BBT; 31 in ZFMK (photo by D. Stüning); 32 in HNHM (photo by Zs. Balint &amp; G. Katona)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089303/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[377,480,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[377,480,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[495,576,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,185,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[205,1382,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Polymixis spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 30, 33–35 in BBT; 31 in ZFMK (photo by D. Stüning); 32 in HNHM (photo by Zs. Balint &amp; G. Katona)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089303/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) by the somewhat less elongate medial ventral process of the antrum and the somewhat wider ductus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,532,618,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Distribution and bionomics</emphasis>
. The species is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[872,1009,619,645]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boursin, Ch." box="[1026,1187,618,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" pagination="298 - 301" refId="ref8940" refString="Boursin, Ch. (1956) Uber die Gattung Lophotyna Hps. (Lep. Phal. Zenobiinae), Nebst Beschreibung einer neuen Art aus Dr. H. Hones China-Ausbeuten und Angaben uber Hydraecia osseola (= hucherardi Mab.) (Beitrage zur Kenntnis der &quot; Agrotidae- Trifinae &quot;, LXXXVII (87 )). Zeitschrift der Wiener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 41, 298 - 301. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1956">Boursin 1956</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1209,1304,619,645]" name="Pakistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. &amp; Weigert, L." pageId="3" pageNumber="25" pagination="237 - 275" refId="ref9262" refString="Hacker, H. &amp; Weigert, L. (1990) 1. Ubersicht uber das Artenspektrum in Nordpakistan (Karakorum, Westhimalaya) im September und Oktober. Esperiana, 1, 237 - 275. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1990">Hacker &amp; Weigert 1990</bibRefCitation>
) and north-western 
<collectingCountry box="[532,590,655,681]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">India</collectingCountry>
(Jammu &amp; Kashmir) (
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[845,990,655,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" pagination="326 - 380" refId="ref9773" refString="Moore, F. (1881) Descriptions of new genera and species of Asiatic Lepidoptera. Proceedings of the Scientific Meetings of the Zoological Society of London, 1881, 326 - 380. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1881. tb 01292. x" type="journal article" year="1881">Moore 1881</bibRefCitation>
). Adults are on the wing in late autumn (October and November) and generally common in their habitats which are the partly forested slopes at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[151,309,727,753]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" unit="m" value="2500.0" valueMax="3000.0" valueMin="2000.0">2000–3000 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
